Basic installation
------------------

  1. To compile the program type:

    make all

  2. You can remove the program binaries and object files by typing:

    make clean

Code documentation
------------------
 
To generate the code documentation the Doxygen must be installed. 
Just type:
  
  make documentation  

and the documentation will be generated and put in folders latex and html.
 
Requirements
------------

  1. ROOT (http://root.cern.ch) with properly paths

  2. gcc  

  3. Doxygen (www.doxygen.org) only if you want to generate 
     the code documentation

  4. BOOST packages
  
  5. libpqxx (connection between framework and database) [1]
  
  6. libconfig++ [2]

Tested Platforms
----------------

  1. Ubuntu x86_64 GNU/Linux
    gcc 4.6.3
    ROOT v5.32
    
  2. Ubuntu 12.04.1 LTS 2013 i386 GNU/Linux
     gcc (Ubuntu/Linaro 4.6.3-1ubuntu5) 4.6.3
     ROOT v5.34/18

Annotation
----------------

  [1]
  Official website:
    https://pqxx.org/development/libpqxx/
  Documentation:
    http://pqxx.org/devprojects/libpqxx/doc/4.0/html/Reference/a00001.html
  Installation [Ubuntu]:
    sudo apt-get install libpqxx-3.1
  Other packages related to libpqxx:
    http://packages.ubuntu.com/lucid/libpqxx-dev

  [2]
  Official website:
    http://www.hyperrealm.com/libconfig/
  Documentation:
    http://www.hyperrealm.com/libconfig/libconfig_manual.html
  Installation:
    sudo apt-get install libconfig++

Requirements installation
----------------

sudo apt-get install libboost-all-dev
sudo apt-get install libpqxx-3.1
sudo apt-get install libpqxx3-dev
sudo apt-get install libconfig++
